I cant remember exactly now, it happend a few weeks ago, but I do remember that I got dispelled by some mob and it didnt remove my first buff, it removed my last. So instead of loosing jboot sow I lost some DS or other more or less useless buff someone gave me (I can recall being surprised when I lost the last buff but that I didnt care to much about it).<br>
<br>
So, the question is, how does it cancel anyways? The most recently casted buff, the olderst buff, the first or last buff, or just a random one? I think I read somewhere that it nowadays just picks a random one.<br>
<br>
To get back to your statement, no matter which buff/effect it starts with it will continue through all buffs until you are stripped bare (if you recast it enough times), except for effects that cant be dispelled (ressurection effect, warder icon). <p>Dannor Stoutwise 42 cleric<BR>
